               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18660611-name-522" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18660611-name-522" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18660611-name-522" type="surname" value="COWDERY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18660611-name-522" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE JANE"></interp>CHARLOTTE JANE COWDERY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Samuel Howarth Cowdery, of 21, Hanover-square, Lambeth—on the evening of 23d April I fastened up my house safely when I went to bed—I was awoke about 6 in the morning by the police, found he back window had been broken, the sash let down, and a part of the window taken right out, so as easily to admit the body of a person into the kitchen—I lost a number of things—these (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) are them, they were found in the garden—I had put them in the copper the previous night, and the best had been picked out and taken away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
